<TITLE> Zia Fertiliser Factory shuts production </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbaria, June 16 (bdnews24.com)  Zia Fertiliser Factory at Ashuganj shut down its urea production units Friday night on mechanical glitch. Habibullah Chowdhury, general manager of the factory, said engineers were working on a war footing to repair the leakages in the ammonia plant compressor, a task that might take two to three days. The fertiliser factory has suffered 18 shutdowns since an overhaul in August at a cost of Tk 60 crore. bdnews24.com/corr
